SINGLE-PHASE k=2 polyphase (pk_k2, k_idx==0 only, L=1500, Nyquist=250Hz) at WIDE channels (96 192 384). Same parent-window count as the k=1 baseline; each window decimated by 2. RF=311 sub-samples × 2ms = 622 raw-ms (kernels=31/8/8, strides=8/4/4). Compares directly to apr26_multiseed_k2_wide (multi-phase, same kernels/channels) — divergence isolates the phase-repetition contribution from the pure downsampling effect.